{{For|the geopolitical term|Balkanization}}
'''Balkinization''' is a law blog focused on [[Constitution of the United States of America|constitutional]], [[First Amendment to the United States Constitution|First Amendment]], and other [[civil liberty|civil liberties]] issues. The weblog was created in 2003 by [[Jack Balkin]], a professor of [[United States constitutional law|U.S. constitutional law]] at [[Yale Law School]]. ''Balkinization'' has been critical of the [[George W. Bush Administration|Bush Administration's]] record on civil liberties issues in the [[War on Terrorism|Global War on Terror]] following [[9/11]]. As of June 2017, the weblog has had approximately 11 million visitors since its creation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sitemeter.com/?a=stats&s=s15balkinization|title=Balkinization|website=SiteMeter}}</ref>
==Notable contributors== Notable contributors include: {{div col}} *[[Ian Ayres]] *[[Stephen Griffin]] *[[Andrew Koppelman]] *[[Marty Lederman]] *[[Sanford Levinson]] *[[Gerard Magliocca]] *[[Rick Pildes]] *[[Mark Tushnet]] {{div col end}}
